<h1>Neil J. Holliday</h1>
<p>University Professor.</p>
<p>Born and educated in England, he came to Canada in 1975. Since 1977, Neil has been in the Department of Entomology at the University of Manitoba, and is currently the Department Head. His research interests are in the ecology of insects in forests, beaches, and agricultural systems, and in the biological control of insects. He teaches agroecology and insect ecology.</p>
<p>His articles for the Manitoba Historical Society:</p>
<blockquote>
<p><a href="../mb_history/51/criddle_n.shtml">Norman Criddle: Pioneer Entomologist of the Prairies</a><br>
<i>Manitoba History</i>, <a href="../../info/pubs/mb_history/51.shtml">Number 51, February 2006</a></p>
</blockquote>
<p><em>Page revised: 24 April 2011</em></p>
